{
  "_comment": "MOCK of SOURCE 1: the on-chain state, shaped exactly like the Donation / DonationFactory contracts (branch contractDonation). The frontend reads these via ethers.js: the campaign list = DonationFactory.getDonations() (address[]); per campaign the Donation getters (donationGoal, totalDonations, start, end, currentStatus, currentMilestone, validators, milestones, neededVoteMajorityInBps, ...). Amounts are the chain's NATIVE coin (donate() takes msg.value; no ERC-20 token). Joined to projectMetadata.json by `address` (the unique project id). Only raw on-chain values live here — anything the UI shows that looks computed is DERIVED in projectsService: 'days left'/'time left' from `end`; milestone absolute amounts from `percentage`*goal; milestone 'status' from paid/readyToBeApproved/currentMilestone+currentStatus; project laufend/abgelaufen from currentStatus+end; approvals-needed from neededVoteMajorityInBps; donor COUNT from the length of the `donors` address list (a mapping has no on-chain count). Milestone `percentage` is in basis points and sums to 10000. INVARIANT (Spende → Stimme → Auszahlung): validators only vote once the goal is reached (currentStatus === 'Payout'); while 'Funding' every milestone has readyToBeApproved=false and 0 votes.",
